The game is not entirely linear so you do need to use your head to think of the next step, but that's part of what makes it so realistic. Also, unlike other "phone simulation" games where you get to choose between 2-3 answers in your conversations, this game accepts free form text entry. It just feels authentic and I loved the easter eggs

Well done to the developers for an overall brilliant concept!

content: I greatly enjoyed this game due to the nature of its puzzles and its story. The hallmark of a great puzzle/detective game is making you feel satisfied when you solve a puzzle, and this game EXCELS at that. You'll have to visit REAL websites, some of which were created specifically for the game, to figure out what to do. The hacking feels very realistic and the dialogue is very interesting! Highly recommend, this is a gem at this price, CAN'T WAIT FOR CASE 2.

Games imitating text messages are becoming old hat, but this one is incredibly immersive, with a ton of fun to be had with creating your own responses. The gameplay is fun, building in some ARG elements without turning into Google Scavenger Hunt. Plus, the game refreshed my DOS skills!!!!! Seriously, this is one of the best mobile games I've ever played.

This game is bad ass. It keeps you on your toes today is my first night and I wrote down so much info. Its like the first 48, plus cold cases, and hunter rolled up into one game. Not for the weak minded. Grown folks games here

Edit: I'm up to chapter 3 and I'm really enjoying it. Like many others have said, it's very well put together with the different websites you can use as a part of the investigation and that really makes it feel legit. The downside is the speech/texting/emailing because the NPCs responses aren't based on what you say to them, except for in a very general sense of using the correct "keyword". If this could be improved upon it would go a long way to making the experience seamless.

This was an absolutely fantastic experience. It is definitely challenging but it's so rewarding and the dev has put a hell of a lot of thought and work into this, and engages so well with the user base. I really hope they make more of these games, because I need more! So good.

replyContent:
The game should use Android's built options for sound, but Android has a separate one for music and notifications. If your phone is on silent, but your phone's music volume is up, for example, you'll still hear in-game music. 

If this wasn't the case for you, feel free to reach out to us and we'll fix any bugs!

I FINALLY BEAT IT. I've been with you since beta in April, and I finally had a chance to sit down and finish it. This game was everything I wanted from a great mystery game and then some! I am constantly in awe of this game you've created. The puzzles are hard, but not unbearably so, just hard enough to make you want more. Every little snag and roadblock just made me want more. I discovered two optional parts along the way, and I'm still astounded by the depth you put into it. They didn't feel optional once I finished them! They were just another integral part of the story! As a fiction writer by hobby, I appreciate the value of a good story line, and I was blown away by the writing you did here. The story felt so real at times that certain events gave me goosebumps and made my stomach drop. I can only imagine the effort you put into this. I know you've said on Reddit that you aren't ready to make another game in the series right now. Whatever your next project is, just know you've got a beta tester for life right here. If you ever do come back to this series, I'll be waiting. üôÇ Thanks again for a wonderful game!

Fantastic game...exactly what I've been looking for. I can't wait for more! As others have said, there are some things that aren't quite intuitive...but, obviously we finished the game, so nothing was that bad! I didn't like how some of the files required me to install multiple apps to use- or just genuinely didn't function properly on my phone. I think next time all I would suggest is maybe making it a bit more standalone, although, having to have a word document open at most times did encourage me to keep notes..maybe there can be an even mix. (On that note, hey devs, there's a grammatical error in the first email of the final chapter-- in case it wasn't meant to be there. Most of the intentional spelling errors/breaks in conversation/bad grammar made it feel more human, but that one kind of broke it for me.) I LOVE that you're able to type your own responses in-game...and that sometimes going off script actually gets you a proper response..it's a nice break from the (a) or (b) dialogue of other games. Probably the most challenging game of this sort I've come across...so if you're looking for a brain teaser, look no further! It was perfect. 10/10 would play again.

content: Noice

I am not a young man. I have been playing video games since the original 
Space Invaders. Yet I can count on one hand the number of times I've left a 
review for ANY product or service. I will say that this game is in my top 
five of all time. If you like tricky puzzlers that play out in real time, 
this game is for you. The game is very minimalistic. The player operates 
from a fake computer system with an environment similar to pure text Linux. 
There are many times when you need to access real websites (most designed 
convincingly by the author) to complete the mission. Although the game 
begins as a simple murder mystery, it quickly evolves into a dystopian 
nightmare. The author is clever...he has a total command of the realistic 
environment, which juxtaposes hackery, industrial poof press, neuroscience, 
vr, and slanted references to Kafka, entomology, and ancient Greek. 
Brilliant work. Game play duration was long, at least for this geazer. The 
author is available on a Reddit page to provide hints. Cannot wait for 
chapter 2.

into this immersive world. Kudos.

The Vigil Files offers a detailed, robust world of gameplay and interaction as you conduct an in-depth investigation into someone who has disappeared. Some puzzles will be relatively easy, only requiring what you learn in-game, while others might require Internet searches to figure out the solutions. Pay close attention to everything you learn, because anything could help you solve the mystery!

Love this game! The storyline is great and the game play feels so real. 
Would definitely recommend
